Thumbnail














March 31, 2015 10:45 AM Eastern Daylight Time



WEST LINN, Ore.--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Radiant Health Management Corp, which opened the first of 100 planned 
      Radiant Pain Relief Centres in February 2014 in West Linn, named Chris 
      Roberts chief financial officer, a newly formed role for the growing 
      company. Mr. Roberts started his career at KPMG, and most recently 
      served as a senior partner and controller at Vancouver, Wash.-based 
      Audigy Group, where he was part of the executive management team that 
      led growth from $600,000 in revenue in 2005 to approximately $32 million 
      in 2014. During that time, the company established itself as one of the 
      most influential companies in the hearing care industry, and has been 
      ranked numerous times for its growth by various American City Business 
      Journals, Inc. magazine, and others. The Portland Business 
      Journal named Roberts small company CFO of the Year in 2009, 
      and 40 under 40 in 2012.
    


      “We believe that the demand for non-surgical, non-narcotic pain relief 
      in North America, a $600 billion market, presents our business with both 
      an opportunity and a responsibility for an aggressive growth plan,” said 
      P. Brendon Lundberg, president and CEO of Radiant Health Management 
      Corp. “We plan to open 100 Radiant Pain Relief Centres over the next 
      five years, and expect rapid growth in revenues and headcount. 
      Therefore, the need for fiscal accountability and leadership is 
      essential to achieve that goal and serve the maximum number of patients 
      possible. Chris has the experience to drive the company through that 
      process.”
    

      “Radiant’s business model and market opportunity are familiar to me on 
      many levels,” said Roberts. “It is exciting to be part of a great 
      company with a growing team that has the ability to profoundly impact so 
      many peoples’ lives, many of which have exhausted all other options.”
    

      Lundberg and Roberts anticipate that organic revenue growth will be 
      coupled with outside investment to achieve its growth targets.
    

      “We are in talks with a handful of investors and plan to expand upon 
      that in coming months. The key is when to fund expansion, and when to 
      employ strategic marketing initiatives,” said Roberts.
    

About Radiant Pain Relief Centres


      Radiant Pain Relief Centres are progressive, patient-centric care 
      facilities that are effectively resolving the epidemic of chronic pain, 
      a $600B healthcare and productivity cost in the U.S. Built around an 
      exclusive FDA-cleared technology, scrambler therapy, Radiant Pain Relief 
      Centres are able to create significant or total pain relief in most 
      cases for 30-90 days following therapy without drugs, needles, surgery 
      or side effects. This technology uses the information theory to retrain 
      the brain through neuroplasticity and return the body to a more normal 
      state of nervous system health, achieving significant, lasting pain 
      relief. Delivered in a highly-refined care model, this technology makes 
      the Radiant Pain Relief Centre approach the most effective and appealing 
      way to treat chronic pain. For more information visit www.radiantpainrelief.com.
    


