Michele Madril 
EDUCATION
PENDLETON -- InterMountain Education Service District has hired Michele Madril as a communications specialist.
She replaces Casey White-Zollman, who recently took a position as vice president of communications at Blue Mountain Community College.
Madril will serve as the public information officer for InterMountain and component school districts, working with them to coordinate their communications.
Madril will also manage crisis communication responses, communicate inclement weather and delay notifications, and serve as the liaison between the district and area news media.
In her previous marketing and public relations career, Madril worked in advertising, magazine writing, television production, and nonprofit organizations.
She earned a bachelor's degree in journalism from the University of North Texas.
For the past six years, Madril has been a substitute teacher in the Pendleton School District and for five years worked as director of Christian education and family ministry at First Presbyterian Church in Pendleton.
FINANCE
PORTLAND -- Columbia Bank has appointed John Shepherd as vice president, wealth advisor for the Oregon market.
John Shepherd
Based in Portland, Shepherd will work with Columbia Bank's Trust, Investment Management, Commercial, Retail and Private Banking groups to support overall business development and client service management.
With more than 35 years of experience, Shepherd specializes in institutional and family credit, treasury, and asset allocations. He strives to be a trusted advisor to identify solutions and discover best practices for all clients in Oregon and Southern Washington--from multibillion dollar institutions to multigenerational family needs. 
Shepherd received his master of business administration in finance and accounting from Baruch College, City University of New York.
In his spare time he enjoys spending time with his family, playing golf, tennis and fitness. Shepherd is also preparing his first few books for publication. Since raising two children, he has come to find a passion for educational endowments. In the past he's supported efforts with St. Anselm College, St. Paul's School and Sacred Heart Cathedral Prep School.
Steve Isaak
PORTLAND -- Washington Trust Bank has hired Steve Isaak has as senior vice president and commercial banking team lead for the Oregon region.
Isaak has 25 years of commercial banking experience with US Bank, where he held various roles, including relationship manager and sales manager/commercial team leader. He was distinguished as one of the top 15 commercial bankers in the country for the past three years for revenue production.
Isaak serves as the current chairman of the board for Junior Achievement. He is a Southern California native and graduated from the University of Oregon.
PORTLAND -- Beneficial State Bank recently promoted Randell Leach to regional president of the Pacific Northwest division and Matt Anderson to senior vice president.
Leach, a corporate entrepreneur with over 20 years of experience in financial services, was the bank's chief credit officer prior to taking on this new role. He brings broad expertise in finance, operations, new market development, and the ability to creatively structure and negotiate deals.

More
People on the move

Leach's new role will encompass sales oversight over loans, transactions, deposits, and non-interest income products. Leach will lead Beneficial State's efforts to expand the bank's service area and mission in the Pacific Northwest.
The Portland resident also serves on the EarthAdvantage board of directors
Anderson has worked in commercial lending for 15 years, with extensive experience in client services and managing commercial loan portfolios with complete underwriting ability.
The Portland resident also serves on the Playworks board of directors.
HEALTH
PORTLAND -- Conversa Health has closed a $2.5 million seed round with top-tier healthcare angel investors and appointed industry veteran Daniel Dean as chief technology officer.
Daniel Dean
The company also announced the formation of a Medical Advisory Board.
The capital will be used to expand Conversa's Digital Checkup service with leading distribution partners in care management, population health and customer relationship management.
Dean is responsible for all engineering and product management. He will lead Conversa's talented team of Health IT engineers in building out a robust product roadmap for its expanding user base.
Dean was the chief information officer for Health Share of Oregon. He also helped pioneer electronic health records at MedicaLogic/GE, and has held product and technology leadership positions at Responsys, WebMD and Press Ganey.
Conversa's newly formed Medical Advisory Board, under the leadership of chief medical officer Dr. Danny Sands, a practicing primary care physician at Beth Israel Deaconess, will create clinical content for the company's Digital Checkup platform.
New advisory board members include Dr. Joseph P. Kannam, a cardiologist at Beth Israel Deaconess, and Dr. Lyle Mitzner, an endocrinology specialist at the Joslin Diabetes Center.
All three distinguished physicians hold academic appointments at Harvard Medical School. 
Stephen AcostaKeene Studio, LLC 
PORTLAND -- The Portland Clinic has hired Dr. Stephen Acosta to work in its downtown Portland center's Urgent Care Department.
Acosta was born and raised in Los Angeles and made UCLA School of Medicine the choice for his higher education.
After interning in Virginia, he returned to Los Angeles to practice and lived in Redondo Beach for almost 20 years, until he and his wife and decided to settle in Portland in 1996.
Although Acosta is board certified in emergency medicine and has practiced such for over 30 years, his career has been comprised of a wide variety of practices and services -- occupational health, medical legal review, house calls and even local rock doc (medical services at music and film venues). The overall goal of his medical care is to help people return to the best possible function with a blend of science, humanism and art.
Outside of medicine, you can find the doctor working on his latest project: building a chipping/putting green on his home property.
VANCOUVER -- Victoria King has been named PeaceHealth's first system chief nursing officer. She will begin serving in the role May 4.
Victoria King
King is currently the chief nursing officer for Memorial Hermann-Texas Medical Center.
Originally from California, she is board certified as a Nurse Executive Advanced, holds masters' degrees in health care administration and nursing, and is a co-founder of the Global Nursing Conference.
In her new role, she will work with nurses, system and community leaders, physicians and others to build a strong standardized nursing care model throughout PeaceHealth.
WEST LINN -- Radiant Health Management Corporation, which opened the first of 100 planned Radiant Pain Relief Centres in February 2014 in West Linn, named Chris Roberts as chief financial officer, a newly formed role for the growing company.
Roberts will be responsible for fiscal leadership at the growing healthcare company including pricing and revenue oversight, investor relations, allocation of funds toward marketing initiatives, and investor reporting
Chris Roberts
Roberts started his career at KPMG, and most recently served as a senior partner and controller at the Vancouver-based Audigy Group, where he was part of the executive management team that led growth from $600,000 in revenue in 2005 to approximately $32 million in 2014. 
The Portland Business Journal named Roberts Small Company Chief Financial Officer of the Year in 2009, and 40 under 40 in 2012.
-- Compiled by Vickie Kavanagh
