Management Team




P. Brendon Lundberg, President & CEO, Board Member

Brendon co-founded Radiant Pain Relief Centres in part as a result of his own struggle with chronic pain. Combining a mission to cure chronic pain with deep experience in healthcare management, marketing, business development and sales, Brendon and Dr. David Farley opened Radiant Pain Relief Centres in West Linn in 2014. Following the success of the first center, they are laying out a plan for expansion to open new centers in new markets. Brendon holds a BS in business marketing and an MBA from University of Phoenix’s main campus in Phoenix, AZ. 
Brendon’s wife, Rachel, is the owner of Lundberg Yoga Teacher Training Program, and teaches at the Gudmestad Yoga Studio and Stafford Hills Club. They have three children and live in the Portland suburb, West Linn.

 

Dr. David Farley, Chief Medical  Officer
David Farley, MD is a co-founder and medical director of Radiant Pain Relief Centres, where he oversees treatment, clinical development and innovation. In this role, Dr. Farley also leads Radiant’s Medical and Science Advisory Board. The board is comprised of medical and academic thought leaders with expertise in pain, and a strong desire to improve and expand treatment options. Dr. Farley has treated patients for nearly 30 years in his family practice in West Linn. He  knows the challenges of dealing with chronic pain, along with the limitations of treatment options previously available. 
Dr. Farley earned his medical degree from the joint Harvard-MIT Health Sciences & Technology program. Dr. Farley and his wife, Ann, live in West Linn where they raised five children and have numerous grandchildren. 


 

Christopher Roberts, Chief Financial Officer 


Chris joined Radiant in March 2015 to provide financial leadership for the company including development and execution of corporate strategy, financial performance management, and investor relations and reporting. He started his career at KPMG, and most recently served as a senior partner and controller at the Audigy Group in Vancouver, Washington. 
Chris has received numerous accolades as part of Audigy’s executive management team. The Portland Business Journal named Chris’ small company CFO of the Year in 2009, and 40 under 40 in 2012. He was born and raised in Oregon, graduated from the University of Portland, and lives in Brush Prairie, Washington with his wife, Heather and their four children.  
 

 

Board of Directors
 
Edward Brennan, Ph.D., Chairman
Dr. Brennan is a trained biochemist turned entrepreneur who has participated in the development, management and financing of new medical technology ventures for more than 30 years. He has held several executive leadership and board positions in medical diagnostics, cardiology, urology and more. He has been involved in more than a dozen IPOs, mergers or acquisitions. 
Dr. Brennan has served on the board of directors of several private companies, and was on the board of trustees of Goucher College, Baltimore, Maryland. He currently serves on the board of Integral Spine Solutions and is the lead independent director of Kilroy Realty Corp. Dr. Brennan holds B.A. degrees in chemistry and biology and a Ph.D. in biology from the University of California, Santa Cruz, California. 

 
 
Thomas Rota, Board Member
Mr. Rota is the managing member at Formational Ventures in Palo Alto, California He is an expert in corporate finance and capitalization strategies for startup and emerging growth companies. He began his career in finance with The Ford Motor Company and Kimberly Clark, before moving to Silicon Valley where he evolved his finance experience into venture-backed companies. Since then, he has lead several companies through growth and initial public offering (IPO) in both chief financial and chief information officer roles. He has raised more than $300 million in capital financing. Mr. Rota received his B.B.A. and M.B.A. degrees in finance from George Washington University. He resides in Palo Alto, California 
 


Advisory Board
Wallace A. Glausi,  Attorney at Law
David Scott, Angel Investor/CPA 
Phil Lundberg, Training & Development Expert  
 
 


















 
